node.text:
Dinner Tonight is a next level casserole. What do you think? 🥘🤤

Baked Cauliflower Mac N Cheese Casserole by @mariofabbrichef 

RECIPE:

Servings: 6-8
Time: 1 hr 15 min cooking

Ingredients:
1 diced onion
4 diced celery stalks
1 c diced fennel
3/4 c oat milk
1/2 c flour
1/4 c water
2 c shredded dairy-free cheese
1 serving macaroni quinoa noodles
1 head cauliflower chopped into ½ inch pieces
1/2 loaf of sourdough bread cut into pieces
S & P

Directions:
1.) In a large pan, sauté the onion, celery and fennel. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper. If it starts to stick to the bottom, add min 1/4 c water. Cook about 10 minutes on medium-low.
2.) In the same pan, add in oat milk and flour. Stir and let cook for 10 more minutes on medium-low.
3.) Cook the noodles about 30% of the way (3 minutes).
4.) In a large bowl; mix together the mixture from the pan with the cauliflower, noodles and cheese.
5.) Add mixture to an oven safe casserole tray. Bake in the oven for 35 minutes at 390°F.
6.) Stir and top with sourdough bread. Bake for 15 more minutes at 390°F.

#dinner #recipes #foodie #plantbased #mariofabbri #chef #cooking #foodreels #foody #casserole #macncheese #pasta #fallrecipes
